ontroversy remains a significant cultural and diplomatic issue, with ongoing debates about the legal and ethical aspects of cultural property and heritage."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"fdf5f332-2747-4553-8e90-117e1ba1dc49_755046656":0.12212895584194332,"b6746fc6-bfc0-4d50-b37c-f497296fac8d_113494911":0.0945624699085219},"text":"The Elgin Marbles, also known as the Parthenon Sculptures, were removed from the Parthenon in Athens by Lord Elgin in the early 19th century and are currently housed in the British Museum."},{"citations":{"b6746fc6-bfc0-4d50-b37c-f497296fac8d_113494911":0.0945624699085219,"46a868b5-4c39-40ee-86d5-cbb777b24031_322002796":0.07281667369349328},"text":"Greece has long demanded their return, arguing that they were stolen and are integral to their cultural heritage."},{"citations":{"b6746fc6-bfc0-4d50-b37c-f497296fac8d_113494911":0.0945624699085219,"99f51daf-328b-42a9-9222-36aafe7a4b22_464486141":0.08685378276171114},"text":"The UK maintains that they were legally acquired under the laws of the time."},{"citations":{"b6746fc6-bfc0-4d50-b37c-f497296fac8d_113494911":0.0945624699085219,"92673347-9486-4c3f-a1d5-089cbaf4e1a2_1039697535":0.08892542182695926},"text":"Efforts for resolution have included proposals for cultural exchanges, where Greece would loan other treasures to the British Museum in exchange for the Marbles' return."},{"citations":{"99f51daf-328b-42a9-9222-36aafe7a4b22_464486141":0.08685378276171114},"text":"However, UK law currently prevents the permanent return of the Marbles."},{"citations":{"92673347-9486-4c3f-a1d5-089cbaf4e1a2_1039697535":0.08892542182695926,"99f51daf-328b-42a9-9222-36aafe7a4b22_464486141":0.08685378276171114},"text":"Recent discussions have considered loan agreements, allowing the Marbles to be displayed in Greece temporarily, but these have not yet resulted in a permanent solution."},{"citations":{"299192ce-8529-44c6-8a6d-3f62f5fc3703_223421099":0.08764415348661636,"25730d40-5bfc-41b5-a011-b31dcb46cf2b_86545786":0.